=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Recorder_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark mixed sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 101 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 100.5793
  harmonic_decay_rate: 2.0304
  harmonic_regularity: 0.3391
  pitch_clarity: 24.5967
  inharmonicity: 0.8846
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -19.3894
  resonance_freq: 344.5312

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Recorder Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Recorder.html
// Tags: Recorder, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
{ SinOsc.ar(
    SinOsc.ar(
        XLine.kr(1, 100, 5)).exprange(*XLine.kr([20, 800], [7000, 200], 10)
    )
   ) * 0.1

}.play;
s.record(duration: 10);
)
